approve(address,uint256).notice: Grant another address the right to transfer token via takeOwnership() and transferFrom().

balanceOf(address).notice: For querying balance of a particular account

getMovie(uint256).notice: Returns all the relevant information about a specific movie.

takeOwnership(uint256).notice: Allow pre-approved user to take ownership of a token

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Owner initates the transfer of the token to another account

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Third-party initiates transfer of token from address _from to address _to

params._to: The address to be granted transfer approval. Pass address(0) to  clear all approvals.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Token that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

createContractMovie(string).details: Creates a new Movie with the given name.

createPromoMovie(address,string,uint256).details: Creates a new promo Movie with the given name, with given _price and assignes it to an address.

params._tokenId: The tokenId of the movie of interest.

setCEO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the CEO. Only available to the current CEO.

params._newCEO: The address of the new CEO

setCOO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the COO. Only available to the current COO.

params._newCOO: The address of the new COO

params._tokenId: The ID of the Token that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

tokensOfOwner(address).details: This method MUST NEVER be called by smart contract code. First, it's fairly  expensive (it walks the entire Movies array looking for movies belonging to owner),  but it also returns a dynamic array, which is only supported for web3 calls, and  not contract-to-contract calls.

params._owner: The owner whose cryptomovie tokens we are interested in.

params._to: The address for the token to be transferred to.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Token that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

params._from: The address for the token to be transferred from.
params._to: The address for the token to be transferred to.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Token that can be transferred if this call succeeds.
